<h1>Client/Server Computing</h1>

<p>By: Jerome</p>

<h2>What is the client/server model?</h2>

<p>The client/server model acts as a core network which provides a service to clients using the web. These services could include web-browsers, gaming software, email software, and online shopping along with many other things. The clients request data from the service providers.</p>

<h2>Advantages of the client/server model</h2>

<p>Major advantages of the client/server model are</p>

<ol>
	<li>Security:Providing security to the clients so they don't have forign users accessing their data but also making sure clients change their passwords regularly. 
	<li>Management: Clients are able to make sure that the software they use will be managed correctly by keeping constant updates and patches, but also making sure it is secure and has backups.s
	<li>Accessibility: Making sure the client can access the servers
</ol>

